caption: New menu is amazing.  Even the garlic knots are to die for.  Pizza better than pizza parlors and half the price.  They even have 3 different kinds of marinated jalepeno peppers (ginger marinated is the bomb).

My wife and I's long standing disagreement on which cheese is best, Cheddar (I thought this was obvious), or American Cheese, has been won. And it is American Cheez.  This has been our new favorite bar. We first went just before covid started back in the normal times. We had a great time inside, played some pinball, watched some sports, drank some beers. And enjoyed the crowd. The bartenders and owner are all great to talk to too.  Since covid, they've got great outside seating on a nice corner that has become a fixture of our weekends. The draft beer is always cold and at a good price. We struggle to find good west coast (non juicy) IPA's on draft, and they always have Lagunitas IPA.  On the weekends, their $5 thin crust pizza is supreme. You can get a similar pizza elsewhere for $12-14 dollars and be less satisfied. It is frankly a problem for the ongoing battle of "can I still fit in my pants". Respect to their pizza maker. We love you man.  The best week was during early voting. We sat outside having a beers, watching all the voters in line, biding our time for when the line was short. Not a lot of work got done that week by us, but we had a great, inspirational time.
Staff if discussing.

This is definitely a dive bar. We met some friends here. There were lots of board games, which one could play with friends in the bar. There was an over sized, huge movie screen with a movie playing. And the best part of the trip to this bar was that we each received a free, plate size pizza with every drink we ordered. We had four beers and 4 pies. I believe the very friendly bartender told us that it is customary for each patron to receive 1 pie with your first drink. It was very cozy, and small. There was a large crowd when we got there. Lots of fun. There was a lot of street parking. It looked like most of the patrons were from the neighborhood. We had a fun time. And the prices were reasonable. We would go back

I can't say I hate this place because I appreciate the kitsch but it boils down to posters of pop stars and celebrities from the 70s-present, though the drinks are strong. Apparently there is some sort of pizza and drink special but I didn't experience that at 9-10pm on a Friday night. I'd think a Friday night would mean they'd have more than one bartender to handle the shouting crowd (shouting at one another, thankfully). If you want a silly place to get a drink, stop by, but keep going if you don't have the patience for a college-type bar. I miss you, Bar 4.
